PARIS, Feb 6 (Reuters) - The board of Nissan (7201.T) has also voted in favour of reshaping its alliance with French carmaker Renault (RENA.PA), a source said on Monday. The agreement, which will retool the two-decade-old alliance, had already got the backing from Renault's board on Sunday. It will be formally unveiled on Monday in London. Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.